ol.li: The Lock: The LOCK instruction prefix triggers the lock_signal. In modern CPUs, this doesn't physically lock the pins of the chip but uses the MESI cache coherency protocol to gain "Exclusive" ownership of the cache line.
The Handshake: The ALU COMPARATOR performs a hardware-level comparison. If the result is a match, the commit_gate is electronically allowed to update the cache line.
The Guarantee: No other core can read or write to 0x7FFEE100 during this window because their own mesi_logic would report the line as "Invalid" or "Busy".
